21#include <limits.h> /* for CHAR_BIT */
22#include "mpc-impl.h"
23
24static void
25mpfr_const_log10 (mpfr_ptr log10)
26{
27 mpfr_set_ui (log10, 10, MPFR_RNDN); /* exact since prec >= 4 */
28 mpfr_log (log10, log10, MPFR_RNDN); /* error <= 1/2 ulp */
29}
30
31
32int
33mpc_log10 (mpc_ptr rop, mpc_srcptr op, mpc_rnd_t rnd)
34{
35 int ok = 0, loops = 0, check_exact = 0, special_re, special_im,
36 inex, inex_re, inex_im;
37 mpfr_prec_t prec;
38 mpfr_t log10;
39 mpc_t log;
40
41 mpfr_init2 (log10, 2);
42 mpc_init2 (log, 2);
43 prec = MPC_MAX_PREC (rop);
44 /* compute log(op)/log(10) */
45 while (ok == 0) {
46 loops ++;
47 prec += (loops <= 2) ? mpc_ceil_log2 (prec) + 4 : prec / 2;
48 mpfr_set_prec (log10, prec);
49 mpc_set_prec (log, prec);
50
51 inex = mpc_log (log, op, rnd); /* error <= 1 ulp */
52
53 if (!mpfr_number_p (mpc_imagref (log))
54 || mpfr_zero_p (mpc_imagref (log))) {
55 /* no need to divide by log(10) */
56 special_im = 1;
57 ok = 1;
58 }
59 else {
60 special_im = 0;
61 mpfr_const_log10 (log10);
62 mpfr_div (mpc_imagref (log), mpc_imagref (log), log10, MPFR_RNDN);
63
64 ok = mpfr_can_round (mpc_imagref (log), prec - 2,
65 MPFR_RNDN, MPFR_RNDZ,
66 MPC_PREC_IM(rop) + (MPC_RND_IM (rnd) == MPFR_RNDN));
67 }
68
69 if (ok) {
70 if (!mpfr_number_p (mpc_realref (log))
71 || mpfr_zero_p (mpc_realref (log)))
72 special_re = 1;
73 else {
74 special_re = 0;
75 if (special_im)
76 /* log10 not yet computed */
77 mpfr_const_log10 (log10);
78 mpfr_div (mpc_realref (log), mpc_realref (log), log10, MPFR_RNDN);
79 /* error <= 24/7 ulp < 4 ulp for prec >= 4, see algorithms.tex */
80
81 ok = mpfr_can_round (mpc_realref (log), prec - 2,
82 MPFR_RNDN, MPFR_RNDZ,
83 MPC_PREC_RE(rop) + (MPC_RND_RE (rnd) == MPFR_RNDN));
84 }
85
86 /* Special code to deal with cases where the real part of log10(x+i*y)
87 is exact, like x=3 and y=1. Since Re(log10(x+i*y)) = log10(x^2+y^2)/2
88 this happens whenever x^2+y^2 is a nonnegative power of 10.
89 Indeed x^2+y^2 cannot equal 10^(a/2^b) for a, b integers, a odd, b>0,
90 since x^2+y^2 is rational, and 10^(a/2^b) is irrational.
91 Similarly, for b=0, x^2+y^2 cannot equal 10^a for a < 0 since x^2+y^2
92 is a rational with denominator a power of 2.
93 Now let x^2+y^2 = 10^s. Without loss of generality we can assume
94 x = u/2^e and y = v/2^e with u, v, e integers: u^2+v^2 = 10^s*2^(2e)
95 thus u^2+v^2 = 0 mod 2^(2e). By recurrence on e, necessarily
96 u = v = 0 mod 2^e, thus x and y are necessarily integers.
97 */
98 if (!ok && !check_exact && mpfr_integer_p (mpc_realref (op)) &&
99 mpfr_integer_p (mpc_imagref (op))) {
100 mpz_t x, y;
101 unsigned long s, v;
102
103 check_exact = 1;
104 mpz_init (x);
105 mpz_init (y);
106 mpfr_get_z (x, mpc_realref (op), MPFR_RNDN); /* exact */
107 mpfr_get_z (y, mpc_imagref (op), MPFR_RNDN); /* exact */
108 mpz_mul (x, x, x);
109 mpz_mul (y, y, y);
110 mpz_add (x, x, y); /* x^2+y^2 */
111 v = mpz_scan1 (x, 0);
112 /* if x = 10^s then necessarily s = v */
113 s = mpz_sizeinbase (x, 10);
114 /* since s is either the number of digits of x or one more,
115 then x = 10^(s-1) or 10^(s-2) */
116 if (s == v + 1 || s == v + 2) {
117 mpz_div_2exp (x, x, v);
118 mpz_ui_pow_ui (y, 5, v);
119 if (mpz_cmp (y, x) == 0) {
120 /* Re(log10(x+i*y)) is exactly v/2
121 we reset the precision of Re(log) so that v can be
122 represented exactly */
123 mpfr_set_prec (mpc_realref (log),
124 sizeof(unsigned long)*CHAR_BIT);
125 mpfr_set_ui_2exp (mpc_realref (log), v, -1, MPFR_RNDN);
126 /* exact */
127 ok = 1;
128 }
129 }
130 mpz_clear (x);
131 mpz_clear (y);
132 }
133 }
134 }
135
136 inex_re = mpfr_set (mpc_realref(rop), mpc_realref (log), MPC_RND_RE (rnd));
137 if (special_re)
138 inex_re = MPC_INEX_RE (inex);
139 /* recover flag from call to mpc_log above */
140 inex_im = mpfr_set (mpc_imagref(rop), mpc_imagref (log), MPC_RND_IM (rnd));
141 if (special_im)
142 inex_im = MPC_INEX_IM (inex);
143 mpfr_clear (log10);
144 mpc_clear (log);
145
146 return MPC_INEX(inex_re, inex_im);
147}
